         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">[9 Aug. 1870 ¶ Dear Hector] ¶  ¶ […] ¶  ¶ By this mail or a close after mail for California […] ¶ I send a boz for Capt. Fairchild with Fieldglass, &amp; some books that Willy sends to his friends in the ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">70.08.09</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">Joseph Hooker to James Hector</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Hector papers, Museum of New Zealand, Wellington.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>[9 Aug. 1870</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Hector]</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[…]<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Not relevant.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>By this mail or a close after mail for California […]<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">four illegible words.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>I send a boz for Capt. Fairchild with Fieldglass, &amp; some books that Willy sends to his friends in the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Sturt</hi>
               </seg>. I am right glad to hear that Haast is doing better. My experience of all these Germans is, that they must be kept in their place. Their good education &amp; general knowledge rapidly gets them good scientific posts to begein with — this demoralized them &amp; after a few years they resent everything, &amp; try to override everyone. Haast has done excellent work &amp; is capable of more, but probably only under good management.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[…]<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Not relevant.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
